data.title: Ethnicity of Celebs
data.text:
Place of Birth: Rome, Italy

Date of Birth: November 9, 1974

Ethnicity: Italian

Family Info: Giovanna Mezzogiorno is a critically acclaimed Italian actress.

She was born to actors Vittorio Mezzogiorno and Cecilia Sacchi. Her father was from Naples and her mother from Milan. Giovanna’s maternal grandparents was Italian writer Filippo Sacchi, born in Vicenza, Veneto.

Photo by Prphotos.com

Birth Name: Jack Finnegan Gilinsky

Place of Birth: Omaha, Nebraska

Date of Birth: September 10, 1996

Ethnicity:

*Ashkenazi Jewish (father)

*Slovak, Czech, German, Irish, English (mother; who converted to Judaism)

Jack Gilinsky is an American singer. He is part of the pop-rap duo Jack & Jack, along with Jack Johnson.

Jack’s father was born Jewish (of Czech Jewish, Polish Jewish, Russian Jewish, and Lithuanian Jewish descent). Jack’s mother is of Slovak, Czech, German, Irish, and English ancestry. Jack’s mother was raised Catholic, and converted to Judaism; she is active in the Omaha Jewish community. Jack was raised Jewish.

Jack is a fifth cousin, once removed, of actress and singer Dianna Agron. Jack’s paternal five time great-grandparents, Shmuel Labe Agronsky and Fruma Chana Bakhrakh, were also Dianna’s four time great-grandparents.

Jack’s paternal grandparents are Larry Gilinsky (the son of Stewart Harold Gilinsky and Frances “Chickie” Bergman) and Deanna Sue Dworkin (the daughter of Edward Dworkin and Eloise Miller). Stewart was born in Iowa, to parents who were born in Iowa and Nebraska, respectively, and all of his grandparents were Czech Jewish immigrants. Frances was born in Nebraska, of Polish Jewish ancestry. Edward was born in Missouri, to a Russian Jewish father and a Lithuanian Jewish mother. Eloise was also Jewish.

Jack’s maternal grandparents are Frank Finnegan (the son of Frances Schroepfer) and Beverly J. Sim (the daughter of Michael Sim, Jr. and Helen Slivka). Michael’s father was born in Pennsylvania, to Slovak parents, and Michael’s mother was Slovak. Helen’s parents were Czech.

Birth Name:Amanda Joy Michalka

Place of Birth:Torrance,California,U.S.

Date of Birth:April,10,1991

Ethnicity:

*German (father)

*German, English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh (mother)

Family Info:Aj Michalka is an American actress and singer. She is the sister of singer/actress Aly Michalka (Alyson Renae Michalka)http://ethnicelebs.com/aly-michalka

AJ’s paternal grandfather was James J. Michalka (the son of Gustave August Michalka and Edna Caroline Loll). James was born in Michigan. Gustave was born in Michigan, to German parents, Frank August Michalka and Mary Venefky. Edna was also born in Michigan, also to German parents, Warner Loll and Henrietta Etta Krahn.

AJ’s paternal grandmother was Betty Anne Martin (the daughter of David Martin and Amelia Yurk). Betty was also born in Michigan. David and Amelia were both immigrants from what is listed as “Russia”. It is likely that they were both of ethnic German descent.

AJ’s maternal grandparents were Charles Malcolm Begley (the son of Newton Phillips Begley and Lula Maude Palmer) and Carmen Louise Wetzel (the daughter of August Wetzel and Harriet Louise McCausland). Aly’s mother’s ancestry includes German, English, Irish, Scottish, and Welsh.

Source: AJ’s paternal grandfather, James J. Michalka, on the 1930 U.S. Census – https://familysearch.org – See more at: http://ethnicelebs.com/aly-michalka#sthash.1s0qKZQQ.dpuf

Genealogy of AJ Michalka – http://wc.rootsweb.ancestry.com

Birth Name:Stephanie Kay Panabaker

Place of Birth:Orange Grove, Texas, U.S.

Date of Birth:May,2,1990

Ethnicity:English, Irish, German, 1/8th Lithuanian, Scottish, Welsh, 1/32 Norwegian, distant Dutch

Family Info:Kay Panabaker is an American actress, she is the young sister of actress Danielle Panabaker.

Kay’s patrilineal line can be traced back to Johann Pfannebecker, who was born, c. 1645, in Alzey-Worms, Germany. Actor Marlon Brando descended from the same man through his mother.

Kay’s paternal grandparents are Harold Jerome Panabaker, Jr. (the son of Harold Jerome Panabaker and Hettie Austine Church) and Mary Sue Miles (the daughter of Farris Marion Miles, Sr. and Autie E. Haney). Danielle’s great-grandfather Harold was the son of Reuben Louis Panabaker and Lillian Annice Jernigan.

Kay’s maternal grandparents are Richard Mayock (the son of Francis “Frank” D. Mayock and Celia M. Pauxtis) and Dolores Ward (the daughter of Grover Blackston Ward and Sarah W. McElwee). Francis’s parents were Irish. Celia’s parents were Lithuanian. Sarah was the daughter of William Joseph McElwee, who was of Irish descent, and of Mary Ellen McGarrity, who was Irish.

Birth Name:Haylie Katherine Duff

Place of Birth:Houston,Texas,U.S.

Date of Birth:February,19,1985

Ethnicity:German, English, Scottish, Scots-Irish (Northern Irish), Welsh, French

Family Info:Haylie Duff is an American actress and singer. She is the elder sister of Hilary Duff.

Haylie’s paternal grandparents were Kenneth Robert Duff (the son of Luke Ralph Duff and Willie Gertrude Roberts) and Mary Pearl Erhard (the daughter of Earl Chester Erhard and Ann Pearl Windrow).

Haylie’s maternal grandparents were Samuel “Sam” Clark Cobb, Jr. (the son of Samuel Clark Cobb and Era Hamil Whitaker) and Amy Beulah Schlemmer (the daughter of Albert L. Schlemmer and Eula Belle Angell). Albert’s parents were German.

Birth Name: Albert Alexandre Louis Pierre Grimaldi

Place of Birth: Monaco-Ville, Monaco

Date of Birth: 14 March 1958

Ethnicity: Monegasque, English, French, German, Irish, Italian, Scottish, Spanish

Family Info:

Albert II is the reigning monarch of the Principality of Monaco. He is the son of Rainier III, Prince of Monaco, and the American actress Grace Kelly. He is married to Charlene (pictured above), Princess of Monaco (Charlene Wittstock).

Albert’s paternal grandfather was Count Pierre de Polignac (the son of Count Maxence de Polignac and Susana Mariana de la Torre y Mier). Count Maxence was the son of Count Charles de Polignac and Caroline Joséphine Le Normand de Morando. Susana was the daughter of Isidoro Fernando de la Torre y Carsí and María Luisa de Mier y Celis. Count is a title.

Albert’s paternal grandmother was Princess Charlotte, Duchess of Valentinois (the daughter of Louis II, Prince of Monaco and Marie Juliette Louvet). Louis II was the son of Albert I, Prince of Monaco and Lady Mary Hamilton. Marie was the daughter of Jacques Henri Louvet and Joséphine Elmire Piedefer.

Albert’s maternal grandfather was John “Jack” Brendan Kelly (the son of John Henry Kelly and Mary Ann Costello). Albert’s great-grandgrandparnets were Irish immigrants. Albert’s great-grandfather John was the son of Brian Kelly and Honora Margaret McLaughlin. Mary was the daughter of Walter Costello and Anne Burke.

Albert’s maternal grandmother was Margaret Katherine Majer (the daughter of Carl Majer and Margaretha Berg). Carl was born in Schloss Helmsdorf, Wurttemberg, Germany, to Johann Christian Karl Majer and Luise Wilhelmine Mathilde Adam, both from Tubingen. Margaretha was born in Heppenheim, Germany, to George Berg, from Walderlenbach, and Elisabetha Röhrig, from Sonderbach.

Source:

Genealogy of Albert II, Prince of Monaco http://www.geni.com/people/Albert-II-Grimaldi-Prince-of-Monaco/6000000003369518706

Birth Name: Rahm Israel Emanuel

Place of Birth: Chicago, Illinois

Date of Birth: November 29, 1959

Ethnicity: Ashkenazi Jewish

Rahm Emanuel is an American politician. A Democrat, he has served as Mayor of Chicago, Illinois, since 2011. He was previously White House Chief of Staff (2009-2010) and a U.S. Representative from Illinois (2003-2009).

Rahm’s parents were/are both Jewish. His father was from Israel and his mother from the United States. He has ancestors who lived in Bessarabia, in Eastern Europe. Rahm’s wife is a convert to Judaism.

Rahm’s paternal grandparents were Ezekiel Emanuel (who was born with the surname “Auerbach”) and Pnyna.

Rahm’s maternal grandparents were Herman/Chaim Smulevitz (the son of Morris Smulevitz) and Sophie Lampert (the daughter of Yankel Lampert and Chia/Haya).

Source: Genealogy of Rahm Emanuel – http://www.geni.com
